FIELD.name: abmaglim
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ESO-specific field not present in the standard ObsCore. 5-sigma limiting AB (Oke) magnitude. The quoted magnitude should refer to the total flux of a point source. Applicable to the following data product type: cube, image, and measurements.

FIELD.name: access_estsize
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Estimated size of the downloaded file in KBytes.

FIELD.name: access_format
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The format of the downloaded file.

FIELD.name: access_url
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A URL that points to the DataLink (VO Standard) service that is used to download the dataset, associated files, their provenance or derived products, etc.

FIELD.name: bib_reference
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: URL or bibcode to the main publication that refers to the data set.

FIELD.name: calib_level
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Calibration level: 0-instrument (raw) data in non-standard format, 1-instrumental (raw) data in standard format, 2-science ready data with instrument signature removed, 3-more highly processed data. Ref. PRODLVL keyword in ESO SDP standard if present, otherwise: set to 3 when dataproduct_type contains token deep or tile, set to 4 for catalogs.

FIELD.name: dataproduct_subtype
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A data-provider/collection specific secondary type, e.g. srctbl or catalog for measurements, tile or pawprint for VISTA images, etc.

FIELD.name: dataproduct_type
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Logical data set type (image, spectrum, visibility, cube, measurements, etc.)

FIELD.name: dp_id
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ESO-specific field not present in the standard ObsCore. The original ESO identifier of the main science file. ObsCore uses obs_publisher_did, which returns the full IVO Identifier. This field can be used to join with other ESO (non-VO) tables, like provenance.

FIELD.name: em_max
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Maximum spectral value observed, expressed in vacuum wavelength in meters; ref. WAVELMAX keyword in ESO SDP standard.

FIELD.name: em_min
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Minimum specrtal value observed, expressed in vacuum wavelength in meters; ref. WAVELMIN keyword in ESO SDP standard.

FIELD.name: em_res_power
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The characteristic spectral resolving power (lambda/delta(lambda)) of the data set. Ref. SPECRES keyword in ESO SDP standard, computed from em_min and em_max when SPECRES not provided := central lambda / delta(lambda) = 0.5*(wavelmin+wavelmax) / (wavelmax-wavelmin)

FIELD.name: em_xel
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Number of elements on the spectral axis.

FIELD.name: facility_name
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Name of the ESO telescope utilised to gather the photons. Possible values are: APEX-12m ESO-3.6 ESO-NTT ESO-VISTA ESO-VLT-U1 ESO-VLT-U2 ESO-VLT-U3 ESO-VLT-U4 ESO-VST MPG/ESO-2.2, and more to come, plus any combination of those (comma-separated), or the word MULTI.

FIELD.name: filter
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ESO-specific field not present in the standard ObsCore. The ESO instrument filter name. ObsCore uses em_min, em_max, and em_res_power to characterise the transmission curve of the bandpass; this field can be used to improve readibility.

FIELD.name: gal_lat
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ESO-specific field not present in the standard ObsCore. Galactic coordinate: latitude; Image/tile/cube centre, barycentre of image arrays in MEF format ; spectroscopic target position; centre of the survey field in case of catalogues.

FIELD.name: gal_lon
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ESO-specific field not present in the standard ObsCore. Galactic coordinate: longitude; Image/tile/cube centre, barycentre of image arrays in MEF format ; spectroscopic target position; centre of the survey field in case of catalogues.

FIELD.name: instrument_name
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Name of the instrument(s) utilised to gather the data; if the data set combines multiple instruments, usually the value MULTI is assigned.

FIELD.name: last_mod_date
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Time stamp of last modification of the metadata

FIELD.name: multi_ob
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ESO-specific field not present in the standard ObsCore. A flag, either M or S. M-Multi OB means that the exposures from different telescope visits have been combined together; S-Single OB means that the product is the result of either a single exposure, or of the combination of exposures taken during the same visit, hence with similar atmospheric conditions, airmasses, etc.

FIELD.name: n_obs
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ESO-specific field not present in the standard ObsCore. Number of observations participating into this data product.

FIELD.name: o_calib_status
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Level of the calibration of the observable (e.g. flux).

FIELD.name: o_ucd
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Nature of the observable within the data set, expressed as an Uniform Content Descriptor (IVOA standard).

FIELD.name: obs_collection
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The name of the data collection the data set belongs to.

FIELD.name: obs_creator_did
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The original file name as assigned by the data producer, in form of a IVOA identifier.

FIELD.name: obs_creator_name
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The Principal Investigator either of the team that provided the data set to ESO through the Phase 3 process, or of the observing team in case the data have been certified by ESO.

FIELD.name: obs_id
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: In case multiple data sets are available for an observation, e.g. with different calibration levels, the obs_id value will be the same for each data set the observation comprises. The obs_id should remain identical through time for future reference.

FIELD.name: obs_publisher_did
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: IVOA dataset identifier for the published data set. It must be unique within the namespace controlled by the publisher.

FIELD.name: obs_release_date
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The date when the data set becomes public.

FIELD.name: obs_title
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: It should contain a brief description (displayable in less than one line of text) specifying in scientific terms the content of the dataset.

FIELD.name: obstech
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ESO-specific field not present in the standard ObsCore. Technique used during the observation. Normally, OBSTECH should be adopted from the keyword HIERARCH ESO DPR TECH of the original data.

FIELD.name: p3orig
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ESO-specific field not present in the standard ObsCore. Possible values: EDP or IDP. EDP is for products prepared and certified by the astronomical community, IDP is for products generated and certified by ESO.

FIELD.name: pol_states
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A list of the polarisation states present in the data set. It is serialised as a concatenated list of the possible values: {I Q U V RR LL RL LR XX YY XY YX POLI POLA} where the list separator is a slash /. Leading and trailing slashes must always be present; example: /YY/.

FIELD.name: pol_xel
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Number of polarisation states available in the data set.

FIELD.name: proposal_id
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The identifier(s) of the observing programme(s) this data set originates from.

FIELD.name: publication_date
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ESO-specific field not present in the standard ObsCore. The publication date is the time when the product has been made available to the user community (whether under proprietary period or not).

FIELD.name: release_description
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ESO-specific field. It provides the link to the PDF document describing the release content, the originating observations, the calibration and data reduction procedures, the data quality, the data format, and the scientific context of the programme

FIELD.name: s_dec
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Equatorial coordinate: Declination (FK5/J2000); Image/tile/cube centre, barycentre of image arrays in MEF format ; spectroscopic target position; centre of the survey field in case of catalogues. Ref. DEC keyword in ESO SDP standard.

FIELD.name: s_fov
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Angular size of the spatial field of view the photons were collected from.

FIELD.name: s_pixel_scale
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Spatial pixel scale

FIELD.name: s_ra
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Equatorial coordinate: Right Ascension (FK5/J2000); Image/tile/cube centre, barycentre of image arrays in MEF format ; spectroscopic target position; centre of the survey field in case of catalogues. Ref. RA keyword in ESO SDP standard.

FIELD.name: s_region
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The spatial footprint of the data set. For an ESO spectrum, the returned footprint is the position (s_ra,s_dec).

FIELD.name: s_resolution
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The characteristic spatial resolution of the data set; ref. ESO SDP standard: PSF_FWHM for images, SKY_RES for 3d cubes, assumed to be the APERTURE for spectral data.

FIELD.name: s_xel1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Number of elements (e.g. pixels) along the first spatial axis.

FIELD.name: s_xel2
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Number of elements (e.g. pixels) along the second spatial axis.

FIELD.name: snr
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ESO-specific field not present in the standard ObsCore. The average signal-to-noise ratio of a spectrum. Not applicable to other data product types.

FIELD.name: strehl
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Strehl ratio: Ratio of the intensity at the peak of the light distribution of an on-axis point source to the intensity assuming an ideal optical system limited only by diffraction over the aperture. It should be a value between 0 and 1

FIELD.name: t_exptime
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Total integration time per pixel (in seconds); ref. EXPTIME keyword in ESO SDP standard.

FIELD.name: t_max
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Stop time in MJD; ref. MJD-END keyword in ESO SDP standard.

FIELD.name: t_min
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Start time in MJD; ref MJD-OBS keyword in ESO SDP standard.

FIELD.name: t_resolution
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Temporal resolution (FWHM) in seconds; currently defined as := (t_max-t_min)*86400.

FIELD.name: t_xel
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Number of elements along the time axis (currently set to 1 for all observations).

FIELD.name: target_name
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The target name as assigned by the Principal Investigator; ref. Ref. OBJECT keyword in ESO SDP standard. For spectroscopic public surveys, the value shall be set to the survey source identifier, which shall be unique within the survey
